### 2. Node labels must be visible
Every node in the graph must show its filename as a label. Use `nodeCanvasObject` to render both the circle AND the text label (filename without path) on the canvas. Example:
```jsx
nodeCanvasObject={(node, ctx, globalScale) => {
  const label = node.path.split('/').pop() || node.id;
  const fontSize = Math.max(10 / globalScale, 2);
  const nodeSize = Math.max(2, Math.sqrt(node.count + 1) * 2);

  // Draw node circle
  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.arc(node.x, node.y, nodeSize, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
  ctx.fillStyle = nodeColor(node);
  ctx.fill();

  // Draw label
  ctx.font = `${fontSize}px sans-serif`;
  ctx.textAlign = 'center';
  ctx.textBaseline = 'top';
  ctx.fillStyle = '#e2e8f0';
  ctx.fillText(label, node.x, node.y + nodeSize + 2);
}}
```

