f856b3ef-5195-4b07-ae74-e76b19feaeaa.task:
Fix the Architecture tab file details panel showing blank/zero values. The bug is a path mismatch.

Edit `~/.openclaw/extensions/mission-control/web/src/components/pages/ArchitecturePage.tsx`.

## Root Cause
The graph API returns **full absolute paths** (e.g., `/home/alansrobotlab/agents/lloyd-home/repos/openclaw/src/agents/bash-tools.process.ts`).

The `api.architectureRead()` endpoint expects **relative paths** (e.g., `repos/openclaw/src/agents/bash-tools.process.ts`) because the backend does `join(homedir(), normalizedPath)`.

When a graph node is clicked, `handleSelectNodeInTree` passes the full absolute path to `handleOpenFile`, which calls `api.architectureRead(filePath)`. The backend then constructs `/home/alansrobotlab/agents/lloyd-home/home/alansrobotlab/agents/lloyd-home/repos/...` which fails the access check, returning an error. The error is caught silently, so `selectedFile` stays null and all stats show 0.

## Fix
In the `handleOpenFile` function (or in `handleSelectNodeInTree`), strip the homedir prefix from graph node paths before passing to `api.architectureRead()`. 

Add a helper function:
```typescript
function toRelativePath(fullPath: string): string {
  // Strip common home directory prefixes
  const prefixes = ['/home/alansrobotlab/agents/lloyd-home/'];
  for (const prefix of prefixes) {
    if (fullPath.startsWith(prefix)) {
      return fullPath.slice(prefix.length);
    }
  }
  return fullPath;
}
```

Then in `handleOpenFile`, use: `api.architectureRead(toRelativePath(filePath))`

Also apply the same fix to the `FileDetailsPanel` component — the `dependsOn` and `dependedOnBy` links use full paths from graph data, so when clicking them to navigate, they also need conversion.

Better yet: make this dynamic. Add a new state variable for the home prefix, derive it from the graph data (find the longest common prefix of all node paths), and use that for stripping.

Or simplest: update the `api.architectureRead` call to handle both absolute and relative paths — if the path starts with `/`, strip the homedir prefix.

## Build
After editing, rebuild:
```
docker exec lloyd bash -c "cd /home/alansrobotlab/agents/lloyd-home/.openclaw/extensions/mission-control/web && /home/alansrobotlab/.bun/bin/bun run build"
```

Do NOT restart the gateway.

