api.on("before_tool_call", async (event: any, hookCtx: any) => {
    if (ctx.activityResetTimer.value) { clearTimeout(ctx.activityResetTimer.value); ctx.activityResetTimer.value = null; }
    ctx.currentActivity.value = {
      type: "tool_call", toolName: event.toolName,
      startedAt: Date.now(), sessionKey: hookCtx?.sessionKey,
    };
    // Tool blocking now handled by tools.deny in gateway config — no runtime check needed
});
```

### 2. Update `POST /api/mc/tool-toggle` to propagate to gateway config (agents.ts)

When a tool is toggled OFF in the master list:
- Still write to `tools.json` (keeps the master toggle state for the UI)
- ALSO add the tool to `tools.deny` for EVERY agent in the gateway config (`openclaw.json`)
- Write the updated config to disk

When a tool is toggled ON:
- Still update `tools.json`
- ALSO remove the tool from `tools.deny` for every agent in the gateway config
- Write the updated config to disk

